That's my view of it -- what would you expect if you don't encrypt
the router -- and also that piggybacking on a wireless connection is
usually a victimless crime.  (Usually, although -- as you pointed out
-- it might not be victimless if the connection is limited or if the
piggy-backer downloads something illegal that way.)

But it's also worth pointing out that if you *do* leave your door
wide open while you go to the shops, that doesn't invariabllyy give
someone a legal right to go in an pinch some of your stuff.  (It
might make it predictable and inevitable, but that doesn't
necessarily make it legal.)

