&gt; I'm also curious about the flip side (but not with any intent to
&gt; further my life of crime). What if I set up an unsecured wireless
&gt; network on purpose? And then someone starts using it. How would I even
&gt; know? And how easy would it be to capture every keystroke they make and
&gt; read their email and get their credit card numbers and have my way with
&gt; their women?
">

Finding out what network traffic is moving across a network you control
is trivial.  Programs like Ethereal(aka wireshark) can capture all traffic
running across a wire.  Depending on the speed of your connection, a simple
desktop PC would be enough to capture 100% of the traffic.

Given 100% of the traffic and sufficient knowledge, you can reconstruct
the entirety of the session.  If we assume for a moment that no encryption
of any sort is being used, then you can quite literally see exactly what
they saw.

